# Introduction
o9 Market Intelligence is the digital situational awareness needed by digitally enabled businesses. It comprises the information about the consumer behaviour, market structure, cultural events as well as broad economic indicators. This intelligence supplements the internal data generated by operations. Using a 360 degree view of the business results in better decisions.

You can find out more at [o9 Solutions' Website](https://o9solutions.com/solutions/revenue/market-intelligence/)

## Knowledge Hub
The Knowledge Hub is the web service that serves the data and knowledge models for o9 Market Intelligence. This document lists all the APIs of this web service. These APIs require an token that you should request from o9.

## Authentication
We use Bearer authentication with the token signifier being 'ApiKey'. Contact your o9 partner to get your authentication token. The token should be sent in the 'Authorization' key of the HTTP header, formatted as under

***Authorization :*** `ApiKey apikey.fromO9solutions`
   
## Filtering Results
Filter conditions are specified in the form of a JSON object as a query parameter called 'filters'. Some example filters are listed below

***Filter using dimension fields returned in the API***

`[{ "AttributeName" : "City", "Values" : [" Dallas : TX Dallas County", "Boston : MA Suffolk County"] }]`

***Filter using higher level grouping of the dimension fields [Refer to the respective dimension API]***

`[{ "AttributeName" : "Country", "Values" : ["USA", "NLD"], "DimensionName" : "Geo" }]`

***Filter using Named Sets [See list of valid values in the next section]***

`[{ "AttributeName" : "Day", "NamedSet" : "CurrentDay" }]`

***Filter using date ranges***

`[{ "AttributeName":"Day", "DateRanges" : [{"op" : ">=", "value" : "2021-06-01"},{"op" : "<", "value" : "2021-06-03"}], "DimensionName" : "Time" }]`

***Multiple filter conditions***  
The filters object is an array of filter conditions. Multiple filters can be combined together for a more refined search. Some examples:

- Specific values

`[{ "AttributeName" : "City", "Values" : [" Dallas : TX Dallas County"] }, {"AttributeName" : "Day", "NamedSet" : "CurrentDay" }]`

- Ranges

`[{ "AttributeName" : "Country", "Values" : ["USA", "NLD"], "DimensionName" : "Geo" }, { "AttributeName":"Day", "DateRanges" : [{"op" : ">=", "value" : "2020-07-01"}], "DimensionName" : "Time" }]`

## Abbreviations and Initialisms

***Wkly*** - Weekly

***Mthly*** - Monthly

***Qtrly*** - Quaterly

***Yrly*** - Yearly

***NSA*** - Not Seasonally Adjusted

***SA*** - Seasonally Adjusted

***SAAR*** - Seasonally Adjusted Annual Rate
